name: David Letterman
monologue: It's tax season. When I woke this morning and realized it was tax season, I said, My God, didn't we just pay taxes last year?

name: Conan O'Brian
monologue: Hillary Clinton announced she's running for president. Yesterday in Ohio, Hillary popped into a Chipotle and she ordered a burrito bowl with chips and salsa. And on her way out she said, "That locks down the Hispanic vote."

name: Conan O'Brian
monologue: Hillary Clinton is not the first woman to run for president. That title belongs to Victoria Woodhull, who ran for president in 1872. Her running mate was a young, scrappy John McCain.

name: Conan O'Brian
monologue: Jeb Bush welcomed his fourth grandchild. The new Bush grandchild is happy, healthy, and will be running for president in 2048.

name: Conan O'Brian
monologue: Olive Garden has announced that it will provide tablet computers at every table. And next step is providing Italian food.

name: Jimmy Kimmel
monologue: Have we all decided who we're going to vote for president yet? You know you only have 574 days left to figure it out.

name: Jimmy Kimmel
monologue: Hillary Clinton announced that she is running. Then she drove from New York to Iowa in a van. You can't be president of the United States unless you agree to eat a corn dog in front of a small group of farmers.
